index.html.title: DjipEvents
index.html.name: DjipEvents
index.html.summary: A modularized event-handling library for the browser

EventEmitter.html.title: EventEmitter
EventEmitter.html.name: EventEmitter
EventEmitter.html.description: The EventEmitter class provides methods to implement the observable design pattern. It is an abstract class meant to be extended on (or mixed in) to add methods such as on(), off(), emit(), etc.

EventEmitter.html#eventCount.title: <readonly> eventCount :Number
EventEmitter.html#eventCount.name: eventCount
EventEmitter.html#eventCount.description: The number of unique events that have registered listeners

EventEmitter.html#eventNames.title: <readonly> eventNames :Array.<String>
EventEmitter.html#eventNames.name: eventNames
EventEmitter.html#eventNames.description: An array of all the unique event names for which the emitter has registered listeners.

EventEmitter.html#events.title: <readonly> events :Object
EventEmitter.html#events.name: events
EventEmitter.html#events.description: Object containing properties for all events with registered listeners

EventEmitter.html#suspended.title: suspended :boolean
EventEmitter.html#suspended.name: suspended
EventEmitter.html#suspended.description: Whether the execution of callbacks is currently suspended or not

EventEmitter.html#emit.title: emit( event )
EventEmitter.html#emit.name: emit
EventEmitter.html#emit.description: Executes the callback functions of all Listener objects registered for a given event. The functions are passed the specifid value (if present) and the content of the listener's data property (if any). If suspended is true no callback functions will be executed.

EventEmitter.html#getListenerCount.title: getListenerCount( event ) → {Number}
EventEmitter.html#getListenerCount.name: getListenerCount
EventEmitter.html#getListenerCount.description: Returns the number of listeners registered for a given event.

EventEmitter.html#getListeners.title: getListeners( event ) → {Array.<Listener>}
EventEmitter.html#getListeners.name: getListeners
EventEmitter.html#getListeners.description: Returns all the Listener objects registered for a specific event.

EventEmitter.html#hasListener.title: hasListener( The ) → {boolean}
EventEmitter.html#hasListener.name: hasListener
EventEmitter.html#hasListener.description: Returns true if the specified event has at least one listener

EventEmitter.html#off.title: off( event [, callback [, context [, once ] ] ] )
EventEmitter.html#off.name: off
EventEmitter.html#off.description: Removes all the listeners that match the specified type of event and, if specified, other criterias.

EventEmitter.html#on.title: on( event, callback [, context [, once [, data ] ] ] ) → {Listener}
EventEmitter.html#on.name: on
EventEmitter.html#on.description: Adds a listener for a specific event. It returns the Listener that was created and attached to the event.

EventEmitter.html#once.title: once( event, callback [, context [, data ] ] ) → {Listener}
EventEmitter.html#once.name: once
EventEmitter.html#once.description: Add a one-time listener for a given event.

EventEmitter.html#suspend.title: suspend( event )
EventEmitter.html#suspend.name: suspend
EventEmitter.html#suspend.description: Suspends execution of callbacks for the specified event type

EventEmitter.html#unsuspend.title: unsuspend( event )
EventEmitter.html#unsuspend.name: unsuspend
EventEmitter.html#unsuspend.description: Resumes execution of callbacks for the specified event type

Listener.html.title: Listener
Listener.html.name: Listener
Listener.html.description: The Listener class represents a single event listener object. Such objects keep all relevant contextual information such as the event being listened to, the object the listener was attached to, the callback function and so on.

Listener.html#context.title: context :Object
Listener.html#context.name: context
Listener.html#context.description: The context to execute the context function in (a.k.a. the value of this)

Listener.html#data.title: data :Boolean
Listener.html#data.name: data
Listener.html#data.description: Arbitraty data that is going to be passed as the second parameter of the callback function

Listener.html#once.title: once :boolean
Listener.html#once.name: once
Listener.html#once.description: Whether this listener's callback function should only be executed once

Listener.html#suspended.title: suspended :boolean
Listener.html#suspended.name: suspended
Listener.html#suspended.description: Whether this listener is currently suspended

Listener.html#target.title: target :EventEmitter
Listener.html#target.name: target
Listener.html#target.description: The object that emitted the event

Listener.html#remove.title: remove()
Listener.html#remove.name: remove
Listener.html#remove.description: Removes the listener from its target.
